{"id":"math140-deriv_chain210-dr001","cid":"MATH 140","topic":"Differentiation Rules","subtopic":"Chain rule","difficulty":2,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"A cost function is C(x) = ({a}x + {b})^{n}. Find C'({x_val}) using the chain rule.","params":{"a":{"type":"int","min":1,"max":4},"b":{"type":"int","min":1,"max":8},"n":{"type":"int","min":2,"max":3},"x_val":{"type":"int","min":0,"max":3}},"answer_expr":"deriv_chain210","steps":["Chain rule: d/dx[(ax+b)^n] = n·a·(ax+b)^(n-1).","C'(x) = {n}·{a}·({a}x+{b})^{new_n}.","C'({x_val}) = {n}·{a}·({inner})^{new_n} = {answer_deriv_chain210}."],"tags":["business-calculus","chain-rule","cost","derivative"]}
